{"start":{"line":16,"column":1},"end":{"line":16,"column":1}},"key":"silJRQar1B"},{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":1},"end":{"line":16,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"MPAS-Viewer Cookbook","position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":1},"end":{"line":16,"column":1}},"key":"QezAnKFI3B"}],"key":"MoTLNY2dC9"},{"type":"text","value":" aims to provide a comprehensive guide for utilizing MPAS-Viewer, a lightweight and efficient Python-based visualization tool designed specifically for MPAS data. Unlike common approaches that rely on triangulation or iterative polygon construction, MPAS-Viewer operates directly on the native mesh, treating each model cell as the fundamental plotting unit. This approach avoids computationally expensive preprocessing steps and significantly reduces rendering time.","position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":1},"end":{"line":16,"column":1}},"key":"T3teKLW5R5"}],"key":"M2uLbZ1cwI"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":1},"end":{"line":18,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Motivation","position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":1},"end":{"line":18,"column":1}},"key":"fmE96BEz7Q"}],"identifier":"motivation","label":"Motivation","html_id":"motivation","implicit":true,"key":"PwaCHatZvN"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":20,"column":1},"end":{"line":20,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The development of this Pythia cookbook is motivated by the need to make MPAS-Viewer accessible, reproducible, and easy to adopt within the scientific community. By combining clear explanations with practical, executable examples, this cookbook provides users with a guided pathway to rapidly visualize, explore, and analyze MPAS-A outputs. It emphasizes simplicity, performance, and interactivity, enabling workflows that support animations, time exploration, and efficient data interrogation.","position":{"start":{"line":20,"column":1},"end":{"line":20,"column":1}},"k